verses.roman:
aneka 'prasāda' dilā pathe khāibāre
tabe punaḥ raghunātha kahe paṇḍitere

synonyms: aneka prasāda—much prasāda; dilā—delivered; pathe khāibāre—to eat on his way; tabe—then; punaḥ—again; raghunātha kahe—Raghunātha dāsa said; paṇḍitere—to Rāghava Paṇḍita.
translation: He gave Raghunātha dāsa a large quantity of prasāda to eat on his way home. Then Raghunātha dāsa again spoke to Rāghava Paṇḍita.
